<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
11:26
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='675000' id='t-675000'>Institutions hate being told they're obstacles.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='679000' id='t-679000'>One of the first things that happens</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='681000' id='t-681000'>when you institutionalize a problem</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='683000' id='t-683000'>is that the first goal of the institution</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='687000' id='t-687000'>immediately shifts from whatever the nominal goal was</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='689000' id='t-689000'>to self-preservation.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='691000' id='t-691000'>And the actual goal of the institution goes to two through n.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='695000' id='t-695000'>Right? So, when institutions are told they are obstacles,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='698000' id='t-698000'>and that there are other ways of coordinating the value,</span>
